author: seattlepi.com
title: Kansas Aviation Museum to celebrate 25th anniversary
text:
WICHITA, Kan. (AP) â€” The Kansas Aviation Museum is set to host an open house to celebrate its 25th anniversary in Wichita.
The Wichita Eagle ( http://bit.ly/1NBSIga ) reports the museum, which is housed in the former terminal for the Wichita Municipal Airport , will have an open house Thursday. There will be a formal ribbon-cutting ceremony at the event, which is open to the public.
The museum recently completed a $1.3 million renovation project in the 80-year-old building.
___
Information from: The Wichita (Kan.) Eagle, http://www.kansas.com
